"M-My dear Watson"...

269
00:15:07,820 --> 00:15:09,810
Next Nagi's hint.

270
00:15:09,810 --> 00:15:10,720
Video.

271
00:15:12,050 --> 00:15:15,560
So, have you figured out the criminal and the trick behind it?

272
00:15:19,620 --> 00:15:21,530
Um...

273
00:15:21,530 --> 00:15:23,210
Give me a snack.

274
00:15:23,210 --> 00:15:25,810
Oh, I mean, Trick or Treat.

275
00:15:26,780 --> 00:15:29,270
Trick or Treat.

276
00:15:31,380 --> 00:15:33,640
W-Wait, give me candy!

277
00:15:33,640 --> 00:15:34,780
Trick or Treat.

278
00:15:36,790 --> 00:15:40,200
Halloween isn't celebrated around Japan well at all.

279
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:42,150
This is a different kind of trick.

280
00:15:44,700 --> 00:15:47,760
Why are we at a place like this all of a sudden?

281
00:15:47,760 --> 00:15:53,870
It can't be helped. Climax scenes by a cliff are the greatest "must have" in a suspense show.

282
00:15:54,110 --> 00:15:57,510
Everything is perfect if we have Funa**** Jirou.

283
00:15:57,860 --> 00:16:00,070
Allow me to explain the truth behind this case now.

284
00:16:00,540 --> 00:16:01,640
Hey!

285
00:16:01,640 --> 00:16:05,640
The scene of the crime was not that room.

286
00:16:06,980 --> 00:16:11,940
If we assume the crime took place in a completely different room at a completely different inn, everything makes sense.

287
00:16:11,940 --> 00:16:15,890
What do you mean? Explain one piece at a time so it makes sense.

288
00:16:15,890 --> 00:16:16,620
Sure.

289
00:16:20,540 --> 00:16:23,800
First, the criminal met the victim at a certain inn.

290
00:16:26,830 --> 00:16:29,200
Recorded the victim's voice during the incident.

291
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:32,640
After that, took the victim to a room at a separate inn that looks similar,

292
00:16:30,400 --> 00:16:33,290
Wait, wait, wait, it'll show! It'll show! It'll show!

293
00:16:32,640 --> 00:16:37,040
in other words, carried her into that room we were in, and...

294
00:16:33,290 --> 00:16:35,490
Be gentler with me! No, stop!

295
00:16:35,490 --> 00:16:36,450
Gentler!

296
00:16:38,690 --> 00:16:44,840
...made others hear the scream using a timer to think that the crime had just happened.

297
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:44,140
You just heard a scream from the inn, right?

298
00:16:44,140 --> 00:16:44,830
Yes.

299
00:16:46,160 --> 00:16:49,290
Everything was planned to create an alibi.

300
00:16:50,490 --> 00:16:53,170
Here! Here, here! I have a question!

301
00:16:53,170 --> 00:16:54,140
What is it?

302
00:16:54,140 --> 00:16:55,200
Where's the proof?

303
00:16:55,890 --> 00:16:59,500
I think the voice recorder alone is pushing it a little.

304
00:17:00,930 --> 00:17:04,100
The greatest proof is on the video we watched.

305
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:06,700
In here!

306
00:17:06,700 --> 00:17:07,570
Play.

307
00:17:09,620 --> 00:17:10,800
I wonder if it's recording fine.

308
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:11,180
Stop!

309
00:17:12,670 --> 00:17:15,440
I don't see anything suspicious.

310
00:17:15,440 --> 00:17:18,770
Don't you notice something about that wall scroll?

311
00:17:23,040 --> 00:17:26,710
It's completely different from the one in that room.

312
00:17:26,710 --> 00:17:27,940
Exactly.

313
00:17:27,940 --> 00:17:31,960
The criminal wasn't able to keep an eye open for the wall scroll.

314
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:34,670
There are four other mistakes, as well.

315
00:17:34,670 --> 00:17:37,230
Those who get them correct will get-

316
00:17:38,280 --> 00:17:41,510
Coming this far, you all know who the criminal is, right?

317
00:17:44,560 --> 00:17:46,610
I remember one person coming late!

318
00:17:47,760 --> 00:17:50,180
And that individual brought the video, right?

319
00:17:50,630 --> 00:17:55,350
